# Annular Ligament

> The **annular ligament** is a strong ring-shaped band that encircles the **radial head**, holding it against the radial notch of the [[Ulna]] and allowing the radius to rotate freely during pronation/supination.

## 🔗 Key Connections
- **Attachment** — Both ends attach to the anterior and posterior margins of the radial notch of the [[Ulna]]
- **Wraps around** — [[Radial Head]]
- **Related structures** — [[Radius]], [[Ulna]], radiocapitellar joint, proximal radioulnar joint

## 🏥 Clinical Significance
- **Nursemaid's elbow (radial head subluxation)** — Annular ligament slips over radial head in children < 5 years when arm is pulled; treated by supination + flexion maneuver
- **Radial head fracture** — May tear the annular ligament; assess stability after ORIF
- **Posterior interosseous nerve (PIN)** — Deep branch of [[Radial Nerve]] passes through the arcade of Frohse near the annular ligament

## 📍 Location
[[Ligament System]] → Upper Limb → Annular Ligament
